{
  "stem": "17299.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 91,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Then I had to work for a while in the swamp Only Jews were working there.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 91,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then later on, I had to work for a German company reclaiming and recycling.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 91,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we were treated as second class citizen.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 91,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We had to do what they told us, and you could not open your mouth and answer back.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 92,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The first work detail was a contractor who was a member of the SS, and what we had to do, we had to do some road building in a swamp and had to take the rubble from the synagogues, which were destroyed in [INAUDIBLE], and we had to build road from that.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 93,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Let's say as long as you did not step out of line, you were treated like a human being.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 94,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We had rationing cards, and some stores had signs on it, Jews will not be served.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 94,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Other stores, we could get what we had on the ration card.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 94,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But in general, we had no shortage of food till 1941.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 94,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Then it was a different ballgame After we had to wear the Star of David.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 95,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "How can we get out of Germany.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, but there was-- in the beginning, some people could get out.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Germans let you get out till somewhere in 1941, people who could go to the United States, who had relatives who paid for the fare and things like that.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Some could go to Switzerland or Sweden, but very few because Switzerland, we know, was very anti-Semitic during that time.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Sweden, Norway, and Denmark were not anti-Semitic, and Holland was not either, but the Germans took Holland in 1940.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 96,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was a different ballgame after that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 97,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "For nearly a year.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 97,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Then I worked for nearly a year in a swamp.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
